00:00:51.259 --> 00:00:55.849
the relationship between the square footage of a house and the price looks like this.

00:00:55.850 --> 00:00:58.609
Here, you can see that the slopes of the lines that

00:00:58.609 --> 00:01:01.850
best fit each set of points are the same,

00:01:01.850 --> 00:01:06.763
even though this neighborhood has more expensive homes for the same square footage

00:01:06.763 --> 00:01:08.030
this would be accounted for by

00:01:08.030 --> 00:01:12.135
the dummy variable as this space between the two lines is consistent.

00:01:12.135 --> 00:01:15.770
And regardless of the neighborhood the increase would be the exact

00:01:15.769 --> 00:01:19.569
